                                codeExplanation7:`<h3 style="font-size: 1.0em; font-weight: bold; margin: 0.5em 0">The align-grow Property</h3>
                                <p>The <i>flex-grow</i> property defines the ability of an item to grow if necessary. It sets the flex grow factor ( relatively to the rest of the items within a container), which specifies the space that the item should take up in the container when distributing positive space.</p><br>
                                <p>The property takes a unitless value that serves as a proportion.</p><br>
                                <img src="/images/align-grow.png" alt="align-grow" width="100%" height="auto"><br>
                                <p><strong>Note:</strong> Value cannot be a negative number.</p><br>
                                <p>If all items in the container have the same value for flex-grow (for example, 1) then all items have the same size in the container.</p><br>
                                <img src="/images/align-grow-same.png" alt="align-grow-same" width="100%" height="auto"><br>
                                <p>If the size of one of the flex items is different (for example, 2), then this item will take up twice more space relative to the size of the other items (the size of which is set to 1).</p><br>
                                <img src="/images/align-grow-different.png" alt="align-grow-different" width="100%" height="auto"><br>
                                `,
